# The `ExecutionSession` Class Reference

<DoxygenPage pluginConfig={pluginConfig}>

### lookup() {#a9260560ad3aaa612b92cff4bccd3c223}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>void llvm::orc::ExecutionSession::lookup (<a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/orc/#ac17672ae6b70c781cc77713e88d698eb">LookupKind</a> K, <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/aarch64/aarch64promoteconstant-cpp/#a90f8350fecae261c25be85d38b451bff">const</a> <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/orc/#a1a2b573da544cf233d62075a16146245">JITDylibSearchOrder</a> &amp; SearchOrder, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/orc/symbollookupset">SymbolLookupSet</a> Symbols, <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/orc/#adac25fca9fb14b1defe43d18a81c16e8">SymbolState</a> RequiredState, <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/orc/#af196a28010b167850a05fc95aa763418">SymbolsResolvedCallback</a> NotifyComplete, <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/orc/#a417b487970e79367118330a5587c8775">RegisterDependenciesFunction</a> RegisterDependencies)</>}>
Search the given JITDylibs for the given symbols.

SearchOrder lists the JITDylibs to search. For each dylib, the associated boolean indicates whether the search should match against non-exported (hidden visibility) symbols in that dylib (true means match against non-exported symbols, false means do not match).

The NotifyComplete callback will be called once all requested symbols reach the required state.

If all symbols are found, the RegisterDependencies function will be called while the session lock is held. This gives clients a chance to register dependencies for on the queried symbols for any symbols they are materializing (if a <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/orc/materializationresponsibility">MaterializationResponsibility</a> instance is present, this can be implemented by calling MaterializationResponsibility::addDependencies). If there are no dependenant symbols for this query (e.g. it is being made by a top level client to get an address to call) then the value NoDependenciesToRegister can be used.

</MemberDefinition>

Returns the resolved symbol map. If WaitUntilReady is true (the default), will not return until all requested symbols are ready (or an error occurs). If WaitUntilReady is false, will return as soon as all requested symbols are resolved, or an error occurs. If WaitUntilReady is false and an error occurs after resolution, the function will return a success value, but the error will be reported via reportErrors.

### removeJITDylibs() {#acfffb371a8a9e003f43cd5027cbea85d}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>Error llvm::orc::ExecutionSession::removeJITDylibs (std::vector&lt; <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/orc/#a1baadbec01aced37be13a1b86c76397e">JITDylibSP</a> &gt; JDsToRemove)</>}>
Removes the given JITDylibs from the <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/orc/executionsession">ExecutionSession</a>.

This method clears all resources held for the JITDylibs, puts them in the closed state, and clears all references to them that are held by the <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/orc/executionsession">ExecutionSession</a> or other JITDylibs. No further code can be added to the removed JITDylibs, and the <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/orc/jitdylib">JITDylib</a> objects will be freed once any remaining JITDylibSPs pointing to them are destroyed.

This method does <em>not</em> run static destructors for code contained in the JITDylibs, and each <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/orc/jitdylib">JITDylib</a> can only be removed once.

JITDylibs will be removed in the order given. Teardown is usually independent for each <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/orc/jitdylib">JITDylib</a>, but not always. In particular, where the ORC runtime is used it is expected that teardown off all JITDylibs will depend on it, so the <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/orc/jitdylib">JITDylib</a> containing the ORC runtime must be removed last. If the client has introduced any other dependencies they should be accounted for in the removal order too.

Declaration at line <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/executionengine/include/llvm/executionengine/orc/core-h/#l01464">1464</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/executionengine/include/llvm/executionengine/orc/core-h">Core.h</a>, definition at line <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/executionengine/lib/executionengine/orc/core-cpp/#l01684">1684</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/executionengine/lib/executionengine/orc/core-cpp">Core.cpp</a>.
</MemberDefinition>

### OL&#95;completeLookup() {#a72aa0428f1be4bec174659b6a4223243}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>void llvm::orc::ExecutionSession::OL&#95;completeLookup (std::unique&#95;ptr&lt; <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/orc/inprogresslookupstate">InProgressLookupState</a> &gt; IPLS, std::shared&#95;ptr&lt; <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/orc/asynchronoussymbolquery">AsynchronousSymbolQuery</a> &gt; Q, <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/orc/#a417b487970e79367118330a5587c8775">RegisterDependenciesFunction</a> RegisterDependencies)</>}>
OL&#95;completeLookup is run once phase 1 successfully completes for a lookup call.

It attempts to attach the symbol to all symbol table entries and collect all MaterializationUnits to dispatch. If this method fails then all MaterializationUnits will be left un-materialized.
